    Class
    Description
    AboutDialog

    The AddTch class is responsible for displaying the dialog to add or edit a teacher.

    The AdminLog class is responsible for displaying the admin log dialog.

    The main application class for the School Management System.
    AssignmentsPanel
    Panel for managing teacher and subject assignments.
    AttendancePanel
    A panel for managing student attendance.
    AttendanceRecord
    Represents an attendance record for a student in the school management system.
    AuthService
    Handles authentication and session management for administrators.
    ClassesPanel
    Panel for managing class levels in the school management system.
    DashboardPanel
    A panel that displays a visual dashboard with charts summarizing key school statistics, such as student distribution and fee collection.
    DashboardStats
    A data class representing key statistics for the school management dashboard, including total number of students, total number of teachers, and total fees collected.
    DataService
    Handles business logic for data operations like searching, deleting, and fetching.
    DataSource
    Manages the database connection pool using HikariCP.
    DB
    Handles database operations such as connecting, querying, inserting, and updating records.
    FeesPanel
    FeesPanel Class
    FileService
    Handles file-based operations like import/export and backup/restore.
    IconUtils
    Utility class for handling icons and images throughout the application.
    Login
    The Login class is responsible for handling user authentication, including both login and registration functionalities.
    Main
    The Main executor of the App
    MainPanel
    The main panel
    PasswordUtil
    Utility class for hashing and verifying passwords using BCrypt.
    Payment
    Represents a payment made by a student in the school management system.
    ReportsPanel
     
    SchoolClass
    Represents a school class level (e.g., Class 1, Class 2).
    SchoolPanel
    A JPanel that represents the main school panel with tabs for different functionalities.
    Settings
    - The Settings class is responsible for displaying the settings dialog.
    StringUtils
    Contains general-purpose string utility functions.
    Student
    Represents a student in the school management system.
    Subject
    Represents a subject in the school management system.
    SubjectsPanel
    Panel for managing subjects in the school management system.
    Teacher
    Represents a teacher in the school management system.
    TeacherAssignment
    Represents an assignment of a teacher to a subject and class level.
    UIManager
    Manages common UI tasks like showing dialogs, progress bars, and creating fonts.
    ViewPanel
    Panel to view detailed profiles of students and teachers.
